The paper presents a conversational system that uses reinforcement learning to schedule meetings. This involves natural language processing (NLP) to interpret user utterances, which suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the use of reinforcement learning suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The system also involves human-computer interaction (HCI) in the form of scheduling meetings, which suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category. Finally, the system involves information retrieval (IR) in the form of finding available time slots, which suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
